#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.40:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Udāyīsutta"
msgstr "40. With Udāyī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: udāyī → udāyi (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an4.40:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho udāyī brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā …"
" pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho udāyī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Udāyī the brahmin went up to the Buddha, … and said to him:"

msgctxt "an4.40:1.2"
msgid "“bhavampi no gotamo yaññaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti?"
msgstr "“Does Master Gotama praise sacrifice?”"

msgctxt "an4.40:1.3"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi;"
msgstr "“Brahmin, I don’t praise all sacrifices."

msgctxt "an4.40:1.4"
msgid "na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi."
msgstr "Nor do I criticize all sacrifices. …"

msgctxt "an4.40:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpe kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe gāvo haññanti, ajeḷakā haññanti, "
"kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"Take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, "
"and various kinds of animals are slaughtered."

msgctxt "an4.40:1.6"
msgid "evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi."
msgstr "I don’t praise that kind of violent sacrifice."

msgctxt "an4.40:1.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.40:1.8"
msgid ""
"Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā "
"arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.40:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpe ca kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, "
"na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and "
"pigs, and various kinds of animals are not slaughtered."

msgctxt "an4.40:2.2"
msgid ""
"evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi, yadidaṃ niccadānaṃ "
"anukulayaññaṃ."
msgstr ""
"I do praise that kind of non-violent sacrifice; for example, a regular gift "
"as an ongoing family sacrifice."

msgctxt "an4.40:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.40:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā "
"arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.44"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.1"
msgid "Abhisaṅkhataṃ nirārambhaṃ,"
msgstr "A sacrifice at the right time,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.2"
msgid "yaññaṃ kālena kappiyaṃ;"
msgstr "which is allowable and deliberately non-violent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.3"
msgid "Tādisaṃ upasaṃyanti,"
msgstr "is attended by"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.4"
msgid "saññatā brahmacārayo."
msgstr "restrained spiritual practitioners."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: Vivaṭacchadā → vivattacchadā (bj, pts1) | vivaṭṭacchadā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:4.1"
msgid "Vivaṭacchadā ye loke,"
msgstr "The Buddhas—who have drawn back the veil from the world,"

# Accepting BB’s reading of the Pali. But his rendering “transcending destination” is meaningless. “Gati” of course means “place of rebirth”.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:4.2"
msgid "vītivattā kulaṃ gatiṃ;"
msgstr "transcending time and rebirth—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:4.3"
msgid "Yaññametaṃ pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "praise this sacrifice,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: yaññassa → puññassa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.40:4.4"
msgid "buddhā yaññassa kovidā."
msgstr "as they are expert in sacrifice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.40:5.1"
msgid "Yaññe vā yadi vā saddhe,"
msgstr "When you’ve prepared a suitable offering,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: habyaṃ → hutaṃ (bj) | huññaṃ (s1-3, km) | bhavyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.40:5.2"
msgid "habyaṃ katvā yathārahaṃ;"
msgstr "whether as sacrifice or for ancestors,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Pasannacitto yajati → pasannacittā yajanti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:5.3"
msgid "Pasannacitto yajati,"
msgstr "sacrifice it with confident heart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:5.4"
msgid "sukhette brahmacārisu."
msgstr "in the fertile field of spiritual practitioners."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: suppattaṃ → sampattaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:6.1"
msgid "Suhutaṃ suyiṭṭhaṃ suppattaṃ,"
msgstr "When it’s well-gotten, well-offered, and well-sacrificed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.2"
msgid "Dakkhiṇeyyesu yaṃ kataṃ;"
msgstr "to those worthy of a teacher’s offering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.3"
msgid "Yañño ca vipulo hoti,"
msgstr "a sacrifice is truly abundant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.4"
msgid "Pasīdanti ca devatā."
msgstr "and even the deities are pleased."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: Evaṃ → etaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ yajitvā medhāvī,"
msgstr "When an intelligent, faithful person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.2"
msgid "saddho muttena cetasā;"
msgstr "sacrifices like this, with a mind of letting go,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.3"
msgid "Abyābajjhaṃ sukhaṃ lokaṃ,"
msgstr "that astute one is reborn"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.4"
msgid "paṇḍito upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr "in a happy, pleasing world.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.40:7.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.40:7.6"
msgid "Cakkavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.1"
msgid "Cakko saṅgaho sīho,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.2"
msgid "Pasādo vassakārena pañcamaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.3"
msgid "Doṇo aparihāniyo patilīno,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.4"
msgid "Ujjayo udāyinā te dasāti."
msgstr ""
